        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 19 at 8:36AM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 835 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Nevada, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nevada, Sheldon, Montevallo, Walker, Bronaugh, Moundville, Milo, and
Harwood.

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 78 and 94.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
